parameters: Chancellor: Knight, step forward.
──Yes, sir!

Chancellor: Currently, our royal capital Near Lake is in the
midst of chaos. There's political tension with neighboring
countries and monsters threatening our territory from the
surrounding areas.

Chancellor: Among these, the rapidly increasing threat and
expanding damage are due to a large monster nest that has
appeared to the west. Suppressing this calamity and saving
our people is our most urgent task.

Chancellor: Therefore, as you may well know, a large-scale
monster subjugation expedition to the west is currently
being planned in our country.

Chancellor: This time, it has been decided that Princess
Soara, who has inherited the throne from the previous king,
will also accompany the expedition.
That is quite...!
Chancellor: Let me continue.

Chancellor: Of course, she will not be going to the front
lines to fight.

Chancellor: However, considering the scale of the battle and
the march schedule, it's not hard to imagine that it will be
a grueling journey. We will do our utmost, but what concerns
us is the potential decline in morale among the troops,
leading to a decrease in combat effectiveness.

Chancellor: Therefore, this time the Princess herself will
visit the camp to inspire the troops. She will become a
pillar of moral support for them and will surely boost their
morale.

Chancellor: It is her role as the symbol of our nation that
she has decided to fulfill herself on this occasion.
Indeed, it is most admirable, Princess Soara!
Chancellor: However, there is a problem.

Chancellor: It is that the succession of the throne to the
Princess was an urgent matter following the death in battle
of the former king, and it has not been long since then.

Chancellor: While preparations for the expedition are
underway, unfortunately, there are still many among the
troops who are hesitant about whether she is truly a
sovereign worthy of their lives.
What an impudent thing to say...!
00_st_pri_01

Princess Soara: It is my lack of power that is to blame. I
do not wish for my servants to be thought ill of.
My liege... One in your position should not speak so...

If only we had more strength to support you, such things
would never be permitted...
Chancellor: Knight, step forward.
Yes, sir!

Chancellor: As you may know, our kingdom is currently
planning a large-scale expedition to subdue monsters in the
west.

Chancellor: This time, our queen, who has succeeded the
throne from the previous king, will also accompany the
expedition.
That is quite...!
Chancellor: Let me continue.

Chancellor: Of course, she will not be going to the front
lines to fight. However, it is not hard to imagine that the
march will be grueling. What we expect is a decrease in
morale among the troops, leading to a reduction in combat
effectiveness.

Chancellor: However, by having the queen herself present to
inspire them, she will become a pillar of support for the
soldiers' spirits and will surely boost their morale.

Chancellor: She has decided to take on this symbolic role
herself this time.
Indeed, it is most honorable, Your Majesty.
Chancellor: However, there is a problem.

Chancellor: It is that the succession of the throne from the
late king to the current queen was an urgent affair and has
only just taken place.

Chancellor: While preparations for the expedition are
underway, unfortunately, there are still many among the
troops who are uncertain if they truly have a sovereign
worth dedicating their lives to.
What an impudent thing to say...!!

Queen: It is my lack of power that is to blame. Do not think
ill of those who serve us.

The king should not say such things. If only we had more
strength to support you, such things would never be
allowed...

Chancellor: But on the other hand, it can also be said that
we have narrowed down the issues that need to be resolved.

Chancellor: A symbol must be made fitting as a symbol,
indeed.

Chancellor: Therefore, I would like you to find a sacred
banner and a treasure sword for the queen to carry with her
during the march.

Chancellor: The blade's radiance is said to harbor the light
of dawn, a supreme treasure mentioned in the royal family's
traditions. "The Sword of Dawn," I want you to bring it
back.
──...!! The Sword of Dawn, you say...!?
Chancellor: What's wrong? Are you dissatisfied?

No, not at all! It is an honor to undertake such an
important mission; I shall certainly bring it back...!

Chancellor: Do not rush; I am not imposing an impossible
task on you.

Chancellor: As you are well aware, the treasure sword was
lost amidst the chaos of a distant past and its whereabouts
are now unknown. I am not mistaking your loyalty by
commanding you to bring back something that exists only in
legend.

Chancellor: Rather, it is precisely because you are so
trusted by the queen that I wish to entrust this task to you
now.
Could it be...!!

Chancellor: Just now, we captured someone from the frontier
at the royal capital. After talking with him for a bit, he
mentioned some intriguing information.

Chancellor: There's a rumor about a "Sword of Radiance" that
one day washed up in the cave of man-eaters in the frontier
and still lies sleeping deep within it.

Chancellor: If the lost royal treasure were to be found in
your hands, who would doubt that it is a throne worthy of
trust?

Chancellor: First, gather information in the surrounding
area, verify its authenticity, and if possible, recover the
treasure sword quickly.

Chancellor: This is an urgent command and also one that must
be carried out in utmost secrecy. Can I count on you?
Chancellor: ...! Your Majesty...!!

Queen: I am aware that I am placing you in a difficult
position and I ask this of you with that understanding.

Queen: The radiance of the treasure sword is said to lead
the country to peace. Now more than ever, amidst this
turmoil due to my insufficient power, that light is needed
for our nation.
Queen: Knight Reisha. I am counting on your bravery.

An adventure is a knight's honor! I swear upon my name to
fulfill your expectations splendidly!!
Queen: I am counting on you...
